laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially 4.2 x 10^9/L before clozapine; during clozapine treatment remained above 4.0 x 10^9/L until February 2007 when it decreased to 3.7 x 10^9/L, neutrophils at 1.9 x 10^9/L. Then decreased to 2.5 x 10^9/L, neutrophils at 1.3 x 10^9/L in February 2009, and further to 1.9 x 10^9/L with neutrophils at 1.0 x 10^9/L in April 2009.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: WBC count stabilized at 3.5 x 10^9/L a week after discontinuation of clozapine, increased to 4.7 x 10^9/L three weeks later, 5.9 x 10^9/L in May 2011, and remained stable since that time.
